POLICE are investi­gating a report of stalking at a supermarket. Stalking terror for mum POLICE are investi­gating a report of stalking at a supermarket.A 27-year-old woman claimed two men followed her and her newborn baby and three-year-old son around Asda in Linwood.She is believed to have contacted security when she realised the men were pursuing her while she was shopping last Tuesday.The men are believed to have fled the scene, and closed-circuit television images are being reviewed in an attempt to provide more information.It is understood the woman was left badly shaken after the incident and contacted family members to take her home.A police spokes&shy;woman said: &quot;We have received a complaint about the incident and the matter is under investigation.&quot; 